Beijing Stock Exchange Margin Trading Business to Start Next Week - China News
(Reporter Sun Jie) Last night, the Beijing Stock Exchange announced that, with the approval of the China Securities Regulatory Commission, the margin trading business of the Beijing Stock Exchange will be officially launched on February 13, when securities companies that have obtained the margin trading authority of the Beijing Stock Exchange can accept the entrustment of investors to declare margin trading to the Beijing Stock Exchange.
The list of the first 56 stocks subject to margin lending will be determined with January 31, 2023 as the base date for calculation.
The BSE said that the list of stocks subject to margin and the list of securities subject to margin will be published through the "Information Disclosure - Margin Information" section of the BSE's official website to facilitate investors' inquiries.
Margin is an important basic system of the securities market and a more mature trading method in the international securities market.
On September 2 last year, on the occasion of the first anniversary of its establishment, the Beijing Stock Exchange publicly solicited comments on the margin business.
The launch of margin trading on the Beijing Stock Exchange is an important measure to continuously promote the construction of the market system of the Beijing Stock Exchange, improve the trading mechanism and enhance the pricing function of the secondary market.
Margin system is conducive to enrich investors' trading strategies, meet investors' diversified trading needs, promote market price discovery, and further enhance market liquidity.
In the next step, under the leadership of the China Securities Regulatory Commission, the BSE will continue to do a good job in safeguarding the margin business, enrich the trading system tools guided by the needs of investors, improve the relevant supporting mechanisms, and strive to build a first-class exchange serving innovative small and medium-sized enterprises.
